# Architecture Constraints (YAMTAM)

## Hard metric limits
| Metric | Hard limit |
|--------|-----------|
| Function length | 50 lines |
| Parameters | 5 |
| Nesting depth | 3 levels |
| File length | 300 lines |
| Cyclomatic complexity | 10 |

Exceed a limit → refactor/split before delivering.

## Design principles
- Functions do ONE thing. "and" in name = split it
- No abstraction until 3+ repetitions — three similar lines > premature abstraction
- No feature flags or backwards-compatibility shims when you can just change the code
- No error handling for scenarios that cannot happen
- Validate at system boundaries only (user input, external APIs) — trust internal code

## Surgical changes
- Only change what was requested
- Don't "improve" adjacent code, comments, or formatting
- Match existing style, even if you'd do it differently
- Unrelated dead code: mention it, don't delete it

## Plan first gate
Run `/plan` before writing code if ANY of:
- New feature touching 3+ files
- Architecture change
- API endpoint change
- DB schema change
